cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper focuses on the design and implementation of a new CAPTCHA to defend against crowdsourcing human cheating. It involves the analysis of the attacking mechanism of CAPTCHA and proposes a new design principle based on private information to distinguish human Typer from human user. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). 

Additionally, the paper also involves the design of a web interaction and password handling program, which suggests the possibility of belonging to the sub-categories cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The proposed CAPTCHA design also involves the use of a novel generation algorithm with a fuzzy matching method, which suggests the possibility of belonging to the sub-categories cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
